nl.fw.yapool.sql.datasource

Class MockByProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.fw.yapool.sql.datasource.MockByProxy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InvocationHandler
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DataSourceProxy

    public class MockByProxy
extends Object
implements InvocationHandler
    Base class to mock interfaces.
    Usefull in case java.sql-interfaces need to be mocked. These interfaces have changed between Java 1.6 and Java 1.7 which can give compile errors. Proxy-classes do not have this problem: they proxy/mock anything at runtime.
    Author:
    FWiers

      • invoke

        public Object invoke(Object proxy,
            Method method,
            Object[] args)
              throws Throwable
        First calls isObjectMethod(Method, Object[]), if that returns true, invokeObjectMethod(Method, Object[]) is called. Else call(Method, Object[]) is called.
        If the result of any of the called methods mentioned above is null, and the method should return a primitive, the value is converted to 0 or false (see also ProxyUtil.getDefaultInstance(Class).
        Specified by:
        invoke in interface InvocationHandler
        Throws:

      • call

        public Object call(Method method,
          Object[] args)
            throws Throwable
        Overload/extend this method to do something with method-calls. This method gets called by the invoke-method for non-object methods (i.e. toString, hashCode and equals are handled by the invoke method itself).
        If this method returns null but the proxied method requires a primitive return value, the invoke-method will convert null to 0 or false of the correct primitive type.
        Throws:
        Throwable
